      "message": "\u003e \u003e Sure, then you have an \u0027events-forwarder\u0027 instead of an \u0027events-broker\u0027, which is fine.\n\u003e \u003e But still, there needs to be an interface with multiple implementations.\n\u003e \n\u003e \n\u003e The difference here is actually fundamental. We have message-forwarder which is an *application specific* abstraction where some implementations will be pubsub based. This is really different from trying to generalize pubsub systems.\n\nThe *events-broker* abstraction was created to generalize the Gerrit-specific forwarding of events, but I see your point. Is the `com.ericsson.gerrit.plugins.highavailability.forwarder.Forwarder` the application-specific interface that you are planning to implement from scratch for every PubSub implementation?\n\n\u003e \n\u003e The proposed GCP pubsub and AWS pubsub implementations are both going to implement the application specific message forwarder interface but the two implementations may not share anything between them because their APIs are so much different anyway.\n\nGotcha. It would still make sense to have them in separate plugins, though, rather than having all the code in a single repo and a single build.",
