      "writtenOn": "2026-02-04T21:23:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Looks like that x-plugin feature is not officially documented, except what is written its commit message in I63c9b7f2a1aee9d50eb2b0eae64821271d583e61.\n\nMy bad, let me add the proper documentation.\n\n\u003e Anyway, I will take a look at it. It may be a good idea to manage dependencies using this feature.\n\n+1\n\n\u003e Btw, when would you use x-plugin feature vs using a Gerrit module?\n\nI\u0027ve presented the differences between the two in the talk at the Gerrit User Summit 2023 (https://youtu.be/XPAA_06XVGc):\n\n1. Gerrit module, is when you want to *influence, change or replace* one part of Gerrit core (e.g. global-refdb, which replaces the repository manager)\n2. Plugin API, is when you want to expose *a new* interface for allowing two plugins to call each other without having to link each other at compile time.\n\nIn this scenario, a Plugin API (x-plugin) would be preferable, see for instance the replication-api at https://gerrit.googlesource.com/plugins/replication/+/refs/heads/master/BUILD#22.",
